like sometimes I will like leave

00:36:20.010 --> 00:36:21.980
the confines and like see people

00:36:21.980 --> 00:36:23.160
doing that in some other place,

00:36:23.160 --> 00:36:25.023
and I'm like, what are you doing?

00:36:26.240 --> 00:36:28.150
Like getting up or sitting on the table

00:36:28.150 --> 00:36:29.350
to make sure their head is higher.

00:36:29.350 --> 00:36:32.570
Like contrast our, I still remember

00:36:32.570 --> 00:36:34.880
like when our manager Jenny started,

00:36:34.880 --> 00:36:35.830
we were in a meeting with her,

00:36:35.830 --> 00:36:37.650
and she sat on the floor,

00:36:37.650 --> 00:36:39.360
she was the only person
sitting on the floor,

00:36:39.360 --> 00:36:40.740
she sat on the floor and made herself

00:36:40.740 --> 00:36:42.830
as small as possible in
this meeting of managers,

00:36:42.830 --> 00:36:46.198
and I was like, wow, what a contrast.

00:36:46.198 --> 00:36:47.031
- [Rachel] Right.

00:36:47.031 --> 00:36:49.460
- 'Cause I was used to
a lot of the punctuating

00:36:49.460 --> 00:36:51.820
