Actually, speaking sort of towards the men

00:37:49.080 --> 00:37:51.290
of Khan Academy, and
they like all tense up,

00:37:51.290 --> 00:37:52.580
I just saw it, I just felt it.

00:37:52.580 --> 00:37:54.050
I just felt you all like, what?

00:37:54.050 --> 00:37:54.910
What is she gonna say?
(audience laughs)

00:37:54.910 --> 00:37:55.910
No, all good things.

00:37:57.020 --> 00:37:59.090
Do you feel sort of, I feel like so much

00:37:59.090 --> 00:38:00.930
of change is kind of driven

00:38:00.930 --> 00:38:03.670
in workplaces by women, right,
and kind of led by women.

00:38:03.670 --> 00:38:06.150
Do you feel like it's on
women's shoulders alone

00:38:06.150 --> 00:38:08.170
to kind of change work environments?

00:38:08.170 --> 00:38:10.200
How is it that we work

00:38:10.200 --> 00:38:11.790
with the men in our life

00:38:11.790 --> 00:38:14.360
to kind of make things more equitable?

00:38:14.360 --> 00:38:15.740
- Yeah, that's a great question,

00:38:15.740 --> 00:38:17.990
and of course, it's all
of our responsibility

00:38:19.939 --> 00:38:22.760
to make an environment that
is inclusive of everyone.

00:38:22.760 --> 00:38:25.230
And there are so many
things that men can do

00:38:25.230 --> 00:38:27.080
being in that position that they are.

00:38:28.060 --> 00:38:31.610
I admire Andy Murray in the
tennis world, for example,

00:38:31.610 --> 00:38:34.160
because he's done so
much for women in tennis.

00:38:34.160 --> 00:38:36.770
He broke away the first, kind of,

00:38:36.770 --> 00:38:38.620
of the male to say like,
well, why are the women

00:38:38.620 --> 00:38:40.600
making so much less
money than the men are?

00:38:40.600 --> 00:38:42.170
They're working just as hard, right?

00:38:42.170 --> 00:38:45.120
They're playing out here
in the same tournaments.

00:38:45.120 --> 00:38:47.870
He hired a woman coach,

00:38:47.870 --> 00:38:51.660
first male kind of major winner.

00:38:51.660 --> 00:38:55.070
So those kinds of things
make a big difference.

00:38:55.070 --> 00:38:58.193
You know, sometimes I
think folks don't realize.

00:38:58.193 --> 00:39:00.400
Maybe the message that
I would send to all men

00:39:00.400 --> 00:39:04.150
is do it if you can
because you believe in it,

00:39:04.150 --> 00:39:07.160
show it because it makes a difference.

00:39:07.160 --> 00:39:09.920
- I said that the other side is also true.

00:39:09.920 --> 00:39:12.920
There's a real benefit, both to everybody

00:39:12.920 --> 00:39:14.120
across the gender spectrum

00:39:14.120 --> 00:39:16.980
when we're operating in this
way that's more inclusive.

00:39:16.980 --> 00:39:21.660
I mean, I've seen a sigh of relief from,

00:39:21.660 --> 00:39:23.430
men on my team join and realize

00:39:23.430 --> 00:39:26.180
that we're not doing this dominance game,

00:39:26.180 --> 00:39:27.460
and just telling me like,

00:39:27.460 --> 00:39:29.430
oh, this is just such
a breath of fresh air

00:39:29.430 --> 00:39:32.870
because I've been in
all these environments

00:39:32.870 --> 00:39:34.750
where you spend all this
time doing that stuff

00:39:34.750 --> 00:39:36.540
instead of just talking about the content.

00:39:36.540 --> 00:39:38.230
And so everybody benefits.

00:39:38.230 --> 00:39:40.480
I think that's kind of the
curb cut principle of design,

00:39:40.480 --> 00:39:45.480
it's like making it better for
groups that are less served,

00:39:45.680 --> 00:39:47.440
makes it better ultimately for everybody.

00:39:47.440 --> 00:39:49.490
- [Rachel] Yeah, I think
that's very true, right?

00:39:49.490 --> 00:39:51.090
I think everyone just kind of wants

00:39:51.090 --> 00:39:54.510
to be seen and reflected in their work

00:39:54.510 --> 00:39:57.340
and feel that they can
contribute in meaningful ways.

00:39:57.340 --> 00:39:59.300
And I think that the fewer barriers

00:39:59.300 --> 00:40:01.810
that we can do to do that,
I think, everyone benefits.

00:40:01.810 --> 00:40:04.290
The work is better, the people are happy,

00:40:04.290 --> 00:40:06.440
you're able to retain your employees

00:40:06.440 --> 00:40:07.940
because everyone just really feels

00:40:07.940 --> 00:40:10.410
kind of all part of a bigger thing,

00:40:10.410 --> 00:40:12.380
which I think is great.

00:40:12.380 --> 00:40:17.380
So now, I'm going to
