00:50:26.610 --> 00:50:28.450
I can say that in my career,

00:50:28.450 --> 00:50:30.040
I have never said no to somebody

00:50:30.040 --> 00:50:31.360
who's asked me to mentor them.

00:50:31.360 --> 00:50:33.450
I may have had limited bandwidth at times

00:50:33.450 --> 00:50:35.380
and said like, well, this year maybe

00:50:35.380 --> 00:50:37.210
I can spend a little time with you,

00:50:37.210 --> 00:50:38.710
next year, there will be more.

00:50:38.710 --> 00:50:39.690
But I've never said no.

00:50:39.690 --> 00:50:41.130
I don't think I'm an anomaly.

00:50:41.130 --> 00:50:44.640
I think that it's recognizing,

00:50:44.640 --> 00:50:46.980
I think the hard part
may be finding a good fit

00:50:46.980 --> 00:50:48.690
because you need to find someone

00:50:48.690 --> 00:50:50.520
who you're going to resonate with,

00:50:50.520 --> 00:50:51.820
you know, what they're telling you,

00:50:51.820 --> 00:50:54.520
not just somebody who's gonna
give you their guide book,

00:50:54.520 --> 00:50:57.630
like we said, everybody's
style is different and so on.

00:50:57.630 --> 00:51:00.450
But I think you're out and about,

00:51:00.450 --> 00:51:01.790
going to talks, going to meet-ups,

00:51:01.790 --> 00:51:04.970
when you hear someone who is saying things

00:51:04.970 --> 00:51:06.610
that you think resonate with you,

00:51:06.610 --> 00:51:08.980
do not hesitate to go up and ask them

00:51:08.980 --> 00:51:11.770
if they'll consider a
mentorship opportunity

00:51:11.770 --> 00:51:14.350
because usually they'll say yes.

00:51:14.350 --> 00:51:15.630
And if when, what's the worst

00:51:15.630 --> 00:51:18.363
that can happen if they
don't and they say no?

00:51:19.260 --> 00:51:21.102
- I think the other thing is like

00:51:21.102 --> 00:51:22.710
