00:51:30.276 --> 00:51:32.020
in a small amount of time.

00:51:32.020 --> 00:51:33.600
So if you've done a little
bit of work up front,

00:51:33.600 --> 00:51:35.970
and you know what they're about,

00:51:35.970 --> 00:51:37.240
what kinds of things interest them,

00:51:37.240 --> 00:51:39.000
then you can already sort of resonate

00:51:39.000 --> 00:51:41.160
and chat about those things.

00:51:41.160 --> 00:51:45.010
And then it kind of goes
back to the empathetic thing,

00:51:45.010 --> 00:51:47.930
also kind of get an idea of like what are,

00:51:47.930 --> 00:51:51.580
how is this a mutually
beneficial relationship?

00:51:51.580 --> 00:51:53.123
That definitely helps too.

00:51:54.290 --> 00:51:56.460
I think a lot of what we
stand to learn from mentees

00:51:56.460 --> 00:51:58.120
are what kinds of things
are you struggling with

00:51:58.120 --> 00:52:00.370
as you're starting out new,

00:52:00.370 --> 00:52:02.470
or coming up through different levels.

00:52:02.470 --> 00:52:04.530
And like we don't wanna lose touch

00:52:04.530 --> 00:52:06.630
with what those experiences are like

00:52:06.630 --> 00:52:08.880
because then we can't
effectively create systems

00:52:08.880 --> 00:52:10.290
to help support people.

00:52:10.290 --> 00:52:11.123
- [Rachel] Right.

00:52:12.130 --> 00:52:13.970
- But we need to be able
to have those conversations

00:52:13.970 --> 00:52:15.590
in a way that don't feel like, cool,

00:52:15.590 --> 00:52:17.040
so what do you wanna
talk about now, right?

